## Key Design Decisions & Notes

**Architecture Overview:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    JIT Block Cache                       │
│  ARM PC → compiled PPC code (BLOCK_CACHE_SIZE=8192)     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
         ↓ miss                        ↓ hit
┌─────────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────┐
│   compileBlock()     │     │   executeBlock()     │
│  - Decode ARM/Thumb  │     │  - Call as fn ptr   │
│  - Emit PPC words    │     │  - Returns normally  │
│  - Fallback to interp│     └─────────────────────┘
└─────────────────────┘
```

**Register Allocation:**
| ARM | PPC | Notes |
|-----|-----|-------|
| R0-R7 | r3-r10 | PPC volatile (saved in frame) |
| R8-R14 | r14-r20 | PPC non-volatile |
| R15 (PC) | r21 | Non-volatile |
| CPSR | r22 | Non-volatile |
| Interpreter* | r23 | Frame pointer |
| Core* | r24 | Frame pointer |

**Fallback Strategy:** Any unhandled instruction emits a call to `JitPpc_interpFallback()` which syncs state, runs one interpreter step, then reloads state.

