The single root cause of the original error and all secondary issues:

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Core::~Core()` defined in `.cpp` but never declared in `.h` — compiler had already synthesised an implicit destructor, making the explicit definition a redefinition | Add `~Core();` to the `Core` class in `core.h` |
| `goto` in `updateRun()` can skip over variable initialisations, causing `-Wjump-to-label-crosses-initialization` | Replaced with a plain `if/else if` chain writing into a local `newFunc` pointer |
| `jitAvailable` used in `core.cpp` but not declared in `core.h` | Added `bool jitAvailable = false;` to the private section of `Core` |
| `invalidateJitPage` defined in `core.cpp` but not declared in `core.h` | Added the declaration to the public section of `Core` |
